parameters:
Noble Plus: Are you from the Adventurer's Guild? I received
a message from Agonia-san.
Clea: I came to collect medicine to resist Lapis's magic.

Storge of Compassion: Oh, you guys! It's perfect timing,
please take this.

Clea: A round and hard stone... I thought it was some kind
of medicine.

Storge of Compassion: The usage is simple! Just grip it
tightly and crush it right before battle, then scatter it
around!

Thief Nora: Ah, leave it to me! I'm really good at dealing
with simple stuff like that!

Storge of Compassion: It's really strange that you're
always doing thief work...
Thief Nora: Ahaha... I think so too...

Noble Plus: It is an honor to be able to contribute to not
only the Magic Academy but also the Adventurer's Guild.

Noble Plus: Please take care of the subjugation of the
magician Lapis, who has tarnished the name of Kanonas, for
us.

Magician Relm: Leave it to this great genius! I also have a
personal reason to fight, so please count on me.

Noble Plus: That attire... You're from the Academy, aren't
you! I personally assist the magicians as well.

Noble Plus: If we have the chance, I would like to have a
discussion about magic.

Storge of Compassion: Please be careful. Lapis might be in
the place you're going.

Storge of Compassion: It's a medicine with no long-lasting
effects. Use it without holding back once the battle
begins.
Noble Plus: Please take care of the Lapis matter.

Noble Plus: I've heard about your exploits. I would love to
hear your adventure firsthand someday.

Noble Plus: Welcome! Please tell us about your wonderful
adventures and knowledge of magic.
Noble Plus: Now, let me guide you all the way inside.
Noble Plus: First, let's talk about the infamous Lapis.
Thief Nora: H-He was such a creepy person!

Priestess Sophia: I completely agree. The word 'madman'
suits him better than 'villain'.

Mage Relm: We defeated him, but the most difficult part was
finding a way to undo the petrification.

Mage Relm: During the process of chasing after Dokusa-san's
assistant, we...
Mage Relm: W-What is it... It's such a nice place.

Clea: For safety reasons, let's stop talking about Albus-
san.

Noble Plus: If there are circumstances that prevent you
from speaking, it's alright. Considering everyone's
achievements, it's only natural.

Noble Plus: I would like to hear from someone as talented
as Relm-san about the main topic of magical lectures. I'm
looking forward to it.

Mage Relm: Leave it to me! I will guide everyone to the
entrance of the magical abyss!

Mage Relm: First of all, what is magic? It is the technique
of harnessing the power of demons sealed within special
grimoires!

Mage Relm: For that reason, understanding grimoires is
essential! That's why we mages are called readers of books.

Mage Relm: Talent alone is not enough. Knowledge and
intelligence are necessary for the interpretation of magical
grimoires!

Mage Relm: Understanding only decomposition, understanding
only release is not enough. A true mage is someone who can
handle everything, the achiever of the three resolutions.

Mage Relm: And please be amazed! Right in front of you is a
third-floor achiever!\^

Mage Relm: After our journey, I will fully dedicate myself
to magical research. The next Archmage and everyone else
will be facing each other!

Mage Relm: Sigh, please show a little interest in your
friend's conversation...

Noble Plus: You are truly amazing, it feels like standing
in front of a massive library.

Noble Plus: How about it? Shall we take a break and
continue with the lecture?
Mage Relm: Um, I don't mind, but...
Noble Plus: I also want to talk about personal financing.
Noble Plus: Well then, I'll be waiting for you in my room.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble Plus: This town lacks entertainment. Please come and
play along with the discussion about the loan.

Noble Plus: I've heard of your exploits. I would love to
hear your adventure tales directly someday.

events.name: 悪石の魔法使い並列処理

parameters:
Noble Plus guards: Please be careful not to be
disrespectful to Lord Plus.

Noble Plus Guard: Ah, she's beautiful... This is bad, this
is bad!

Noble Plus Guard: I want you to take this as a reminder to
not get distracted while on duty, especially when she's so
beautiful.

Noble Plus Guard: It seems you still have a lot of training
to do.
Mansion Maid: Do you have any business with Master Plus?

Mansion Maid: The young lady magician... hehe, I hope I
meet the expectations of Lord Pulse.
Mansion Maid: Welcome to Lord Plus's mansion.

Noble Plus: Thank you for coming. First, let's talk about
the loan. How about discussing it here?
Mage Relm: Th-This much money... Is it really okay!?

Noble Plus: Considering it as a loan to a promising mage
who we have heard about from the Archmage, this amount is
too small.

Noble Plus: Ideally, we would like to continue providing
loans to Relm-san.

Mage Relm: It's a very happy story, but I can't immediately
return to my research.

Mage Relm: I still want to continue traveling with my
friends...

Noble Plus: Hahaha, it's fine. I have determined that you
are worth that much.

Mage Relm: If you're saying that much, I will definitely
repay you with my research results!

Noble Plus: Let's raise a toast for the bright future of
this wonderful mage.

Mage Relm: I-I don't have many good memories with
alcohol...
Noble Plus: Well, well, it's just a toast, after all.

Mage Relm: Sleeping during a lecture! I can't forgive even
a friend for that, I can't go on without drinking!

Mage Relm: You don't have enough respect for mages! If
everyone was like Mr. Plus, the empire would develop even
more!
Noble Plus: Hahaha, those are kind words.

Noble Plus: By the way, you're quite the drinker, aren't
you?

Mage Relm: I may be treated like a child, but I am a
respectable adult, you know!
Mage Relm: The three people near me are just exceptional!
Noble Plus: Relm-san, would you like some as well?

Noble Plus: It's a unique pleasure of the Medicine City to
drink it dissolved in wine, you know.
Mage Relm: Could that possibly be...?

Noble Plus: I'll have it right away... hehe, the sensation
throughout my body is pleasantly distorting.

Noble Plus: Now, you too... let's enjoy the play of
knowledgeable and cultured adults together.
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Noble Plus: It was a very enjoyable time. I will contact
the Magic Academy regarding future funding.

Noble Plus: This city lacks entertainment. Please come and
play with me while we discuss the funding.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble Plus: I will book accommodations near the mansion.
Everyone, please rest there and take your time.
Do you want to skip the adult scene?

Noble Plus: I am honored that you have come. First, let's
talk about financing and magic lectures.

Noble Plus: Afterwards, let's thoroughly enjoy some adult
playtime.
